HEADWORD: Idiotical
<hw>Id`i*ot"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>idioticus</ets>
ignorant, Gr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>idiotique</ets>. See
<er>Idiot</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Common; simple.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Blackwall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or like, an idiot; characterized by
idiocy; foolish; fatuous; <as>as, an <ex>idiotic</ex> person, speech,
laugh, or action</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idiotically</ent>⟦br⟧
